-- DLA Piper Hires Insurance Attorney William Marcoux From Dewey & LeBoeuf
-- B y   I a n   T h o m a s
-- 2012-02-21T19:12:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-21/dla-piper-hires-insurance-attorney-william-marcoux-from-dewey-leboeuf.html
DLA Piper LLP (1191L)  hired William C. Marcoux, a partner at  Dewey & LeBoeuf LLP (1151L) , as the firm expands
its insurance industry practice.  Marcoux, 55, formerly the co-head of Dewey’s insurance
sector group and a member of its executive committee, has 30
years of experience in complex global insurance industry
transactions, DLA Piper said in a statement. He will join DLA
Piper as a partner, and as the head of its insurance sector
transactions and regulation practice.  “This is a great opportunity for us to strengthen our
sector capability across the firm as Bill’s experience and
relationships are truly global,” Nigel Knowles, joint chief
executive officer of DLA Piper, said in the statement.  DLA Piper, an international  law firm  with more than 4,200
lawyers, was ranked the third-highest grossing law firm in
fiscal 2010 with revenue of $1.96 billion,  according  to the
American Lawyer, a trade publication.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian Thomas in  New York  at   ithomas15@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Hytha at   mhytha@bloomberg.net . 